# Next.js Web Standards

## 1. Project Structure

```
app/           # Next.js App Router pages, layouts, API routes
components/    # React components (see nextjs-component-architecture.mdc)
lib/           # Utility functions, API clients
hooks/         # Custom React hooks
types/         # Shared TypeScript types
```

**Key Rules:**

- No `src/` directory - source at project root
- No barrel exports (`index.ts`) - import directly from files
- Group related files together (colocation)

## 2. Naming Conventions

| Type                | Convention   | Example                         |
| ------------------- | ------------ | ------------------------------- |
| Component files     | kebab-case   | `product-card.tsx`              |
| Component exports   | PascalCase   | `export function ProductCard()` |
| Page files          | `page.tsx`   | `app/products/[slug]/page.tsx`  |
| Custom hooks        | `use` prefix | `useAuth`, `useUser`            |
| Other files         | kebab-case   | `fetch-data.ts`                 |
| Variables/functions | camelCase    | `isLoading`, `handleClick`      |
| Types/interfaces    | PascalCase   | `UserProfile`, `ApiResponse`    |

## 3. Export Patterns

**Default exports:** Only for Next.js special files

- `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`, `not-found.tsx`

**Named exports:** Everything else

- Components, hooks, utilities, types, API handlers

```typescript
// ✅ Component
export function Button({ children }: ButtonProps) { ... }

// ✅ API route
export async function GET(request: Request) { ... }
```

## 4. TypeScript Requirements

- **Forbid `any`**: Use `unknown` with type narrowing
- **Explicit typing**: Props, state, hook returns, complex variables
- **User-facing text as constants**: Prepare for i18n

```typescript
// ❌ Forbidden
function process(data: any) { ... }

// ✅ Required
function process(data: unknown) {
  if (isValidData(data)) { ... }
}

// ✅ User-facing text
const LABEL_SUBMIT = 'Submit'
const ERROR_REQUIRED = 'This field is required'
```

## 5. Server vs Client Components

**Default to Server Components.** Only use `'use client'` when needed.

| Need                    | Component Type |
| ----------------------- | -------------- |
| Data fetching           | Server         |
| SEO content             | Server         |
| Static UI               | Server         |
| `useState`, `useEffect` | Client         |
| Browser APIs            | Client         |
| Event handlers          | Client         |

**Runtime Secrets Pattern:**

```typescript
// Pages that need runtime secrets (not available at build time)
export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic'
```

## 6. Styling Requirements

- **Tailwind CSS**: Primary styling solution (mandatory)
- **shadcn/ui**: All components built from shadcn primitives (mandatory)
- **CSS Variables**: Use for theming
- **Mobile-first**: Responsive design approach

## 7. Performance Optimization

| Feature        | Usage               |
| -------------- | ------------------- |
| `next/image`   | All images          |
| `next/link`    | Internal navigation |
| `next/font`    | Font loading        |
| `next/dynamic` | Lazy loading        |

**Data fetching:**

- Parallel fetches with `Promise.all()`
- Use React Query for client-side state — see `docs/REACT_QUERY_GUIDE.md` for the required pattern
- **All** AEM content **must** use Server Actions as `queryFn` (not `useEffect + fetch`) with server-side `prefetchQuery` + `HydrationBoundary` — no exceptions; see `docs/REACT_QUERY_GUIDE.md#server-actions-pattern-for-aem-content`

## 8. Error Handling

- Early returns for error conditions
- Guard clauses for preconditions
- Error boundaries around async operations
- **Console Logging Policy**:
  - **Client-Side**: All console methods prohibited
  - **Server-Side**: `console.error()` allowed for critical errors; prefer OpenTelemetry for structured logging
  - **Instrumentation**: Console logging acceptable in initialization code

## 9. Anti-Patterns Quick Reference

| Anti-Pattern                                   | Severity | Fix                                    |
| ---------------------------------------------- | -------- | -------------------------------------- |
| localStorage on every state change             | HIGH     | Debounce writes (500ms)                |
| Missing memoization for expensive ops          | MEDIUM   | `useMemo` for >5ms operations          |
| Unbounded list rendering (>100 items)          | HIGH     | Use virtualization                     |
| Sequential API calls that could parallelize    | MEDIUM   | `Promise.all()`                        |
| Missing useEffect dependencies                 | HIGH     | Include all dependencies               |
| Client fetch when Server Component works       | MEDIUM   | Move to Server Component               |
| Index as key for dynamic lists                 | MEDIUM   | Use stable unique ID                   |
| Direct DOM manipulation                        | HIGH     | Use refs, not `document.querySelector` |
| Prop drilling through 3+ levels                | LOW      | Use Context                            |
| PII in localStorage without encryption         | HIGH     | Use HttpOnly cookies                   |
| `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` without sanitization | HIGH     | Use DOMPurify                          |
| API secrets in client code (`NEXT_PUBLIC_`)    | HIGH     | Server-side only                       |
| Interactive div without keyboard support       | HIGH     | Use `<button>` or add handlers         |
| Icon-only buttons without aria-label           | HIGH     | Add `aria-label`                       |
| Form inputs without labels                     | HIGH     | Associate with `htmlFor`               |
| Using `any` type                               | HIGH     | Use `unknown` with narrowing           |
| Non-null assertion without validation          | MEDIUM   | Handle undefined case                  |
| Magic strings/numbers in code                  | MEDIUM   | Extract to named constants             |
| Inline user-facing text                        | MEDIUM   | Extract constants for i18n readiness   |
| `useEffect + fetch` for AEM content            | HIGH     | Use Server Action as React Query `queryFn` + server prefetch + HydrationBoundary — see `docs/REACT_QUERY_GUIDE.md` |

For detailed examples, see `nextjs-patterns.mdc`.

